l">15 小时的有声读物访问</a>，这是最近添加的一项功能，我们怀疑许多订阅者无论如何都不关心。 Spotify 本月早些时候表示，将从 7 月开始将<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-raising-the-cost-of-premium-subscriptions-again-123058485.html">Premium 价格提高</a>至每月 12 美元。</p><p>该基本计划与上个月在英国<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:4;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://uk.news.yahoo.com/sign-spotify-basic-plan-save-140536525.html?guccounter=2" data-original-link="https://uk.news.yahoo.com/sign-spotify-basic-plan-save-140536525.html?guccounter=2">推出的</a>一项计划相呼应。该版本的费用为每月 11 英镑，而包含有声读物内容的 Premium 每月费用为 12 英镑。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>一些人怀疑 Spotify 推出的有声读物有邪恶的动机。本月早些时候，美国国家音乐出版商协会<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/music-publishers-accuse-spotify-of-bait-and-switch-subscription-scheme-235255614.html">要求联邦贸易委员会调查</a>这一举动，甚至称该公司的有声读物整合是“一个通过欺骗消费者和欺骗音乐版税制度来增加利润的计划”。 NMPA 的投诉称，由于有声读物融合，Spotify 明年将少支付约 1.5 亿美元的音乐版税。 Spotify 告诉 Engadget，它没有做错任何事，并否认了这些指控。</p><p> Spotify 在其他领域一直精打细算。去年有报道称，该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-looks-set-to-overhaul-its-royalty-model-next-year-081722667.html">计划彻底改革其特许权使用费模式</a>。据称，该计划的一部分是取消月收入低于 5 美分的曲目的货币化，从而将一些没有固定观众的独立艺术家赶走。</p><p>去年年底，Spotify 还<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-laying-off-1500-employees-081521615.html">解雇了约 9,000 名员工</a>，理由是“我们的财务目标状态与当前运营成本之间存在差距”。</p><p>上线后（发布时尚未），您可以导航到<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:8;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://spotify.com/account" data-original-link="https://spotify.com/account">您的帐户页面</a>，然后“管理您的计划”和“更改计划”并选择“基本”，切换到无有声读物层。如果您是新订阅者，您可以在<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:9;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.spotify.com/us/premium/#plans" data-original-link="https://www.spotify.com/us/premium/#plans">注册</a>时选择基本选项。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/spotifys-basic-plan-returns-to-11-a-month-by-cutting-audiobooks-163804267.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/spotifys-basic-plan-returns-to-11-a-month-by-cutting-audiobooks-163804267.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6257382c-b30e-4259-86a5-154002e7b3c8</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Will Shanklin]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jun 2024 16:38:05 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1718987886</ingested><modified> 2024-06-21T16:38:15+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="786" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2F82070130-2fe8-11ef-bfde-8629622ba825&amp;resize=1400%2C786&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=23cbed7d8e502fb14e1b0095d02399f74c39b5cc" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="786" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2F82070130-2fe8-11ef-bfde-8629622ba825&amp;resize=1400%2C786&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=2e54c50059a337906b2205c7f86303e318aa8be0" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Spotify]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Spo